SIMPLE: instep
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Instep
<hw>In"step</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <altsp>[Formerly also
<asp>instop</asp>, <asp>instup</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The arched middle portion of the human foot next in
front of the ankle joint.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The part of a shoe, boot, or stocking covering the
instep{1}.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>That part of the hind leg of the horse and allied
animals, between the hock, or ham, and the pastern joint.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>instigant</ent>⟦br⟧
